we are really di&s;&s;atisfied in the Fideli|ty
<PB N="15" REF="16">
of the Parties, or no; but be tho&s;e Di&s;|&s;atisfactions
of what Kind &s;oever, it cannot
be Prudence for us to run the Hazards that
in other Ca&s;es might be done.</P>
<P>But to leave this ungrateful Part of the
Subject, it is not &s;aid, or &s;ugge&s;ted
