al&s;o the De&s;ire of all Her Faithful Subjects,
that a Good and La&s;ting Peace &s;hould be
made, has been openly declared; what el&s;e
has a Negotiation been &s;et on Foot for?
Her Maje&s;ty has other Work to do in the
World than to amu&s;e the Nations Abroad,
or Her Subjects at Home, with a Treaty,
if a Peace had not been Her De&s;ign: This is
not a Thing to be dallied with, if the Pious
