Re&s;olutions of making Peace: This brings
us Home to the Teeth of the Party, and
will expo&s;e their Scandalous Practices, and
they may value them&s;elves upon it when
they plea&s;e, it will be but &s;hewing their
own Nakedne&s;s to Po&s;terity.</P>
<P>Her Maje&s;ty having, with mighty
Struggling and Oppo&s;ition, obtained a
Treaty, and Plenipotentiaries from mo&s;t of
<PB N="16" REF="17">
the Confederates to meet for that Purpo&s;e&punc;
New Intrigues were immediately &s;et or
Foot to render all the Meetings and Confe$rences
on the Grand Affair Abortive, a$$
to come to nothing; to this Purpo&s;e, and
the Mea&s;ures for it being concerted, th$$
Emperor on a &s;udden &s;ends his Plenipoten$tiaries
to the Congre&s;s, which he had re$&s;olved
never to do before; it is to be
ob&s;erved, that no &s;ooner were tho&s;e Pleni$potentiaries
arrived, but a New Scene be|gan
to appear, and a different Part was
acted from what they were acting before&punc;
for as they an&s;wered <HI>Cavaillierly,</HI> that they
would never &s;end any Mini&s;ters to the
Meeting, or take any Notice of it, all on a$
&s;udden they were not only come to the
Congre&s;s, but New Conferences, and New
Mea&s;ures, appear'd; the Imperial Mini|&s;ters
