<P><PB N="17" REF="18">
Thus they put off the Time, and &s;u&s;|pended
the Pro&s;ecution of the Peace, as
if they had a Certainty that the Armies
would join, that the Campaign would
begin, and &s;o the Treaty would be cut
in Two by the Sword; believing that if
