order my Army and my Generals to act
on the Defen&s;ive only till you can give
me better Rea&s;ons for carrying on the
War.&endq;</P>
<P>All this is &s;aid upon a Suppo&s;ition that
what the Sc$$dalous S$ribler of fal&s;e
News hath Printed. But can any Man
believe the Account? Is it Rational
to think that Prince <HI>Engene</HI> is &s;o lit|tle
a Man of Breeding as to give the
<HI>Briti&s;h</HI> General &s;uch Language? Ought
not the Writer of &s;uch News to be
brought to the Whipping-Po&s;t for thus
abu&s;ing Prince <HI>Eugene?</HI> Is it in the
lea&s;t likely that Prince <HI>Eugene</HI> would
<PB N="18" REF="19">
have asked the Duke of <HI>Ormond</HI> &s;o
In&s;olent a Que&s;tion on his giving his
Opinion again&s;t Fighting, as, <HI>What do
you do here then?</HI> Every General has his
Liberty in the Council of War to give
his Opinion to what &s;hall be there pro|pos'd
for or again&s;t Fighting: Prince
<HI>Eugene</HI> would not have made that Re|ply
to any Private Colonel, as to &s;ay,
<HI>What do you do here then?</HI> But had not his
Grace many a ready An&s;wer to have re|turned
to &s;uch an In&s;ult as that? Might
he not have &s;aid, &startq;That the Troops of his
Mi&s;tre&s;s were there, and had been there
Nine Year, to give his Ma&s;ter a Crown,
which he had neither Ability to gain
without them, nor Gra$$ude to acknow|ledge
to his Benefactre&s;s now he had got
it?&endq; Might he not have replied, They were
to fight when they &s;aw Occa&s;ion, but
not like Auxiliaries, to fight at his bid|ding?
Might be not have &s;aid, They
were there to fight when Probable Oc|ca&s;ions
pre&s;ented, and when Evident Ad|vantage
pre&s;ented, but not <HI>Alamode de
Blaregnies,</HI> to &s;acrifice the Lives of a Brave
Body of Men to the Glory of a Gene|ral,
and to butcher their Men for the
meer Name of a Victory, as was
done at <HI>Malplacquet?</HI> Many more Ju&s;t
Returns might have been given to a
Sarca&s;m, &s;o Haughty and &s;o Rude as
that; but our General contented him|&s;elf
<PB N="19" REF="20">
to give no other Reply than to &s;hew
his Orders; and this may be a very
good Rea&s;on for any Wi&s;e Men to be|lieve
